            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Our son Potetas has died, aged 8 years, on the 17th of the month of August, during the 19th moon</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--epitaph of Potetas; date of death given according to the 19th day of the moon. Originally assigned by MP to the uncertain / Roman category, Griesheimer argues strongly that this must be a Sicilian epitaph, not a Roman catacomb one, and Ferrua finds ref in Marini, RAC (1974), 432-433 to attribute to 'dintorni di Noto'--></p>
            </div>
